$ The command ps aux | grep kube-api | grep encry
search encryption


process:
create a secret:
k create secret generic <secret-name> --from-literal=<key>=<keyvalue>

verify:
k get secret

show how it's stored in etcd:
ETCDCTL_API=3 etcdctl \
   --cacert=/etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/ca.crt   \
   --cert=/etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/server.crt \
   --key=/etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/server.key  \
   get /registry/secrets/default/<secret-name> | hexdump -C    //| hexdump -C show the data in a confusing way

note: after applying | hexdump -C, in the rectangle area, if you dont see the keyvalue, that means that it's encrypted successfully.







